<h2 id="who-its-for">👥 Who BigCommerce Is For</h2>

**Ideal operators:**

- Multi-location businesses needing centralized ecommerce management
- Operators selling B2B and B2C from the same inventory
- Businesses approaching or exceeding $250K in annual online sales
- Teams with basic technical competence or access to development resources
- Operators prioritizing SEO performance and organic traffic acquisition
- Businesses selling across multiple channels (marketplace + direct)

**Not ideal for:**

- Solo operators under $50K annual revenue (platform is overkill)
- Businesses requiring extensive customization without development budget
- Operators who need hand-holding through every technical decision
- Simple single-product or subscription-only businesses (simpler tools exist)

If you're running a single location with straightforward needs, our [small business ecommerce comparison](/reviews/small-business-ecommerce-platforms) covers lighter-weight options. BigCommerce's power becomes overhead rather than advantage at smaller scale.

